I have a bunch of views using DRF that include something like this. 

The code within `get_queryset` is where the hvad code is

```
class CollectionsRetrieveUpdate(generics.RetrieveUpdateAPIView):
    def get_queryset(self):
        language = self.request.query_params.get('language', settings.LANGUAGE_CODE)
        return Collection.objects.language(language).fallbacks('en-us').all()
    serializer_class = CollectionSerializer
```

I was wondering if I could DRY that up by removing the language/hvad code and putting it into a filter like this 

```
class TranslationFallbackFilter(filters.BaseFilterBackend):
    def filter_queryset(self, request, queryset, view):
        language = request.query_params.get('language', settings.LANGUAGE_CODE)
        return queryset.language(language).fallbacks('en-us')
```

but I get an error of something similar to 

`AttributeError: 'QuerySet' object has no attribute 'language'`

Do I need to use a custom manager to make this work or is there an hvad suggested way to do this?

